        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:00PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 500 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Friars Point, or 8 miles northeast of Elaine,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Helena-West Helena, St Francis National Park, Friars Point, Lake
View, Coahoma, Lula, Huma, Wabash, Moon, Modoc, Preston Place,
Quarles, Oneida, Hoop Spur, Westover, Jeffries, Delta, Matagorda,
Spring Creek, and Helena Crossing.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
